Hi there,

This is Cody from Avada Support.

I’m reaching out regarding your request to adjust the position of the chatbox widget on your store.

At the moment, we noticed that the app is currently turned off on your theme: https://capture.avada.io/i/ZhOLZlssXPuO
So we’re unable to apply the changes yet. Could you please help enable the app on your theme? Once it’s active, we’ll be happy to proceed with the adjustment for you.

Alternatively, below is the CSS code our team prepared to help adjust the position of the chat button, chatbox, and welcome popup. You can apply this by going to the Chatbox section > Advanced: https://capture.avada.io/i/Q5C2LPIijZlC
Then scroll down to the Custom CSS field and add the code here: https://capture.avada.io/i/RZrrfI5GCUpd

.Avada-Faqs_Button {
bottom: 130px !important;
}

.Avada-Faqs_Popup {
bottom: 130px !important;
}

.Avada-FaqsWelcomePopup {
bottom: 190px !important;
}

Additionally, you can adjust the pixel values in the code above to customize the position exactly the way you want.

If you need any assistance along the way, feel free to let us know, we’re always here to help. Thank you!

Best regards,
Avada Support Team

Hi Caracole team, 

This is Jade from the Avada Support Team, and I hope you are doing well. 

I am writing to follow up on your recent request regarding the JavaScript SDK. Please find below the SDK events for the two actions you mentioned:

**1, When the user opens the chatbox:**

$chatty.on(‘chat:opened’, function() {
 console.log(‘Chat was opened’);
});

**2, When the user closes the chatbox:**

$chatty.on(‘chat:closed’, function() {
 console.log(‘Chat was closed’);
});

We highly appreciate your kind patience in the meantime. Our team will keep you posted on the SDK documentation once it is available. 

Regards,
Jade

